1
00:00:06,067 --> 00:00:08,167
<i>She's the only one who managed
to solve our problem.</i>

2
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:11,400
<i>I want Thea reinstated
starting tomorrow.</i>

3
00:00:11,533 --> 00:00:12,667
<i> Vallejo Realty?</i>

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,867
<i>Isn't that our family
company's rival?</i>

5
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,033
<i> If you're interested,</i>

6
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:17,567
<i>we have a great proposal
for you.</i>

7
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:20,500
<i>Thanks for letting me
come back here.</i>

8
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:21,900
<i> I only did it for Dad.</i>

9
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:24,533
<i>Let's just avoid each other
while we're here at the office.</i>

10
00:00:24,667 --> 00:00:25,833
<i> You're sweating.</i>

11
00:00:25,967 --> 00:00:27,500
<i>Don't you feel guilty
about what you're doing?</i>

12
00:00:27,633 --> 00:00:29,233
<i>Edward isn't
exactly innocent either.</i>

13
00:00:29,367 --> 00:00:32,000
<i>I know he still hasn't gotten
over Marj.</i>

14
00:00:32,133 --> 00:00:33,667
<i>I want you to take care
of yourself.</i>

15
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:34,867
<i> Good thing you're here.</i>

16
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:36,967
<i>My child and I now
have extra support.</i>

17
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:39,433
<i>Edward! Are you the one
poisoning my wife's mind</i>

18
00:00:39,567 --> 00:00:40,600
<i>so she'll keep getting
mad at me?</i>

19
00:00:40,733 --> 00:00:42,200
<i>Didn't I tell you not
to bother me?</i>

20
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:43,800
<i> Your wife isn't even here.</i>

21
00:00:43,933 --> 00:00:46,400
<i>I'm sure she's with my husband
right now.</i>

22
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:47,900
<i> No. No.</i>

23
00:00:48,033 --> 00:00:49,533
<i>You can't make me do this again.</i>

24
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:56,167
Ma'am Thea almost...

25
00:00:58,567 --> 00:00:59,633
Hey, keep it down.

26
00:00:59,767 --> 00:01:01,267
Let's just keep that
between us, okay?

27
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:03,233
Of course, Sir.
My lips are sealed.

28
00:01:06,933 --> 00:01:07,833
Oh.

29
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,100
I know what you're thinking.

30
00:01:10,233 --> 00:01:11,867
That I'm back to my old ways
again?

31
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:14,800
That I've gone back
to womanizing?

32
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:18,133
I'm not judging you, Sir.

33
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:20,500
If that were me, I probably...

34
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:24,633
It doesn't matter
what I would've done, Sir.

35
00:01:24,767 --> 00:01:26,933
What matters is that you didn't
do anything.

36
00:01:28,133 --> 00:01:30,733
Ma'am Thea really surprised me
there.

37
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,533
You know,
you can't really blame her.

38
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:37,233
You're a good-looking guy.

39
00:01:37,367 --> 00:01:38,567
You're successful, too.

40
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:40,433
You're focused on work.

41
00:01:40,933 --> 00:01:43,667
It's not surprising Ma'am Thea
would like you.

42
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:48,533
You know what, I think I really
need to cut back

43
00:01:48,667 --> 00:01:51,133
on being such a workaholic.

44
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:54,100
Why don't I listen to my wife?

45
00:01:54,233 --> 00:01:55,767
She's right.

46
00:01:57,267 --> 00:02:00,233
I should be spending more time
with her and our child.

47
00:02:00,367 --> 00:02:02,133
If they were the ones with me
right now...

48
00:02:02,267 --> 00:02:03,400
then maybe...

49
00:02:05,167 --> 00:02:08,567
Maybe I wouldn't have almost
given in to Thea's temptation.

50
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:05,033
I really appreciate how you're
always there for me.

51
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,400
For my family.

52
00:03:13,967 --> 00:03:15,733
Thank you so much, Edward.

53
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:20,533
Sorry.

54
00:03:22,033 --> 00:03:24,133
I didn't mean to make you feel
uncomfortable.

55
00:03:24,267 --> 00:03:25,367
No, no. It's okay.

56
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:28,233
Ah, I should get back
to Jasmine.

57
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,700
I'll walk you there.

58
00:03:30,833 --> 00:03:32,867
No, it's fine,
I've got it.

59
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:36,267
Thanks for the coffee.

60
00:04:06,033 --> 00:04:07,100
Good morning.

61
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,733
Dad, what's this emergency
meeting for?

62
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:30,767
As Chairman Emeritus
of Torrecampo Realty,

63
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:33,933
decided to gather everyone
to talk about

64
00:04:34,067 --> 00:04:36,200
the company's current crisis,

65
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:38,567
the Menagerie Manor Project.

66
00:04:40,133 --> 00:04:42,833
Dad, I've been looking
for a solution.

67
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,467
I already solved it.

68
00:04:46,567 --> 00:04:51,233
The board has decided to hire
someone to help exclusively

69
00:04:51,367 --> 00:04:52,800
with your project.

70
00:04:53,767 --> 00:04:55,033
Ah, what?

71
00:05:04,933 --> 00:05:08,833
Everyone,
this is Aldrin Castelo...

72
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:14,500
the Menagerie Manor Project's
new sales director.

73
00:05:14,633 --> 00:05:16,267
Good afternoon, everyone.

74
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:19,100
I'm Aldrin Castelo
of Castelo Prime Holdings.

75
00:05:20,567 --> 00:05:24,233
Mr. Torrecampo has personally
and humbly asked me

76
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:27,900
and my team to step in and help
you with one of your...

77
00:05:28,967 --> 00:05:31,367
most difficult accounts.

78
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:35,333
And please don't think I'm here

79
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:37,733
to take your jobs
or your commissions.

80
00:05:37,867 --> 00:05:40,733
It's not your fault
that this project

81
00:05:40,867 --> 00:05:43,733
was doomed from the very start.

82
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:48,933
I understand that sometimes...

83
00:05:49,867 --> 00:05:53,900
no matter what we do,

84
00:05:54,033 --> 00:05:55,933
it just can't seem to work.

85
00:05:56,067 --> 00:06:00,600
And this is completely normal
and acceptable in this industry.

86
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,767
That's exactly why I'm here.

87
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:06,233
To help you reach your annual
revenue targets.

88
00:06:06,367 --> 00:06:07,733
Sorry.

89
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:09,433
Sorry to cut you off.

90
00:06:09,567 --> 00:06:13,233
But, Dad, this is ridiculous!

91
00:06:14,067 --> 00:06:16,667
This is my project,
and I'm still the CEO.

92
00:06:17,567 --> 00:06:20,333
Am I not part of the board's
decision-making anymore?

93
00:06:20,467 --> 00:06:21,600
Pao.

94
00:06:22,267 --> 00:06:24,933
This is not the place to be
emotional, son.

95
00:06:25,067 --> 00:06:25,933
Emotional?

96
00:06:26,067 --> 00:06:27,633
Dad, I am not emotional.

97
00:06:27,767 --> 00:06:31,567
I am upset because you didn't
even consult me!

98
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,933
Does my opinion not matter
to this board anymore?

99
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:44,567
You needed help with
this dumb project

100
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:46,233
and we're giving it to you.

101
00:06:46,367 --> 00:06:51,467
The company is more important
than your pride.

102
00:07:16,767 --> 00:07:17,933
Marj.

103
00:07:22,267 --> 00:07:25,433
Ah, I just came here
to apologize.

104
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,400
I didn't mean to make things
feel awkward

105
00:07:29,533 --> 00:07:30,833
between the two of us.

106
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:33,800
It won't happen again.

107
00:07:33,933 --> 00:07:35,567
I promise.

108
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:36,633
It's okay.

109
00:07:36,767 --> 00:07:39,233
It didn't mean anything
anyway, right?

110
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:45,033
Oh, by the way, Marj.

111
00:07:45,167 --> 00:07:48,233
Did you receive the email
from Dr. Marquez?

112
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,800
My friend, the pediatric
hematologist.

113
00:07:50,933 --> 00:07:51,967
Sorry, Edward.

114
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:53,867
I haven't had time to go online.

115
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,033
What did your friend say?

116
00:07:56,700 --> 00:08:00,667
Well, he informed me
that Jasmine qualifies

117
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,667
for the experimental treatment

118
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:05,567
And he's willing to accommodate
both of you.

119
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:06,967
Really?

120
00:08:07,100 --> 00:08:09,267
Yes, but she'll need to be
admitted in Hong Kong,

121
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:14,300
since that's where the equipment
and the medical team are.

122
00:08:14,433 --> 00:08:16,600
So we have to go to Hong Kong?

123
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:35,100
Oh, soliciting isn't allowed
here, Ma'am.

124
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:40,400
Are you saying I look like
a beggar?

125
00:08:40,533 --> 00:08:42,267
Well, if you're carrying
an envelope,

126
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,833
maybe a decent beggar.

127
00:08:50,067 --> 00:08:53,300
Do you really enjoy teasing me
that much?

128
00:08:55,133 --> 00:08:59,167
Why do you look so happy
insulting me?

129
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,900
You're so sensitive.

130
00:09:03,033 --> 00:09:05,600
I just want to lighten up
the mood.

131
00:09:05,733 --> 00:09:08,933
Every time I see you,
you look like...

132
00:09:09,067 --> 00:09:11,400
you know...

133
00:09:11,533 --> 00:09:13,900
like you're carrying the world.

134
00:09:15,467 --> 00:09:16,500
Ah?

135
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,500
Should I thank you for that?

136
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:26,767
Like I'm supposed to be happy
you're insulting me?

137
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:31,800
No, that's not what I meant...

138
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:33,433
- Ah!
- And also...

139
00:09:35,133 --> 00:09:36,067
Teka, Greg.

140
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:36,900
Wait, Greg.

141
00:09:37,033 --> 00:09:40,333
Yes, I accept it.

142
00:09:40,467 --> 00:09:43,167
Fine, I look worn out.

143
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,300
I look like an informal settler.

144
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:50,033
But I don't care
what people say about me.

145
00:09:50,167 --> 00:09:52,133
Because I know who I am.

146
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:54,300
I'm a good mother.

147
00:09:56,233 --> 00:09:59,367
I'm raising my two kids
properly.

148
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:00,733
Yes.

149
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:16,300
Bye.

150
00:10:17,467 --> 00:10:18,833
Mama!

151
00:10:19,833 --> 00:10:20,933
Jobert!

152
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:26,967
- What a sweet kid.
- Hi, Uncle Greg.

153
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:28,367
You're all sweaty.

154
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:29,767
Hello.

155
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:47,267
Rose! Cathy!

156
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,733
Come on!
Is there nobody here?

157
00:10:49,867 --> 00:10:51,200
Where are you?

158
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:52,467
- Yes, Ma'am!
- Yes, Ma'am!

159
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,767
Sorry, Ma'am.

160
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:55,333
- Why are you so slow?
- We didn't hear

161
00:10:55,467 --> 00:10:56,800
you calling, Ma'am.

162
00:10:56,933 --> 00:10:58,133
- Huh!
- Yes, Ma'am, we were packing

163
00:10:58,267 --> 00:10:59,900
the things Ma'am Marj will bring

164
00:11:00,033 --> 00:11:02,033
to the hospital
for Ma'am Jasmine.

165
00:11:02,167 --> 00:11:03,167
So what?

166
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:05,967
Is that more important than
welcoming me?

167
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,600
Why do you prioritize people

168
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:09,167
who aren't even here
all the time?

169
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:10,967
What's your problem, Thea?

170
00:11:11,467 --> 00:11:13,033
Don't take it out on the maids.

171
00:11:13,167 --> 00:11:15,467
If you have a complaint,
confront me.

172
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:18,600
Oh, look who's here.

173
00:11:18,733 --> 00:11:21,633
Marj, I get that
Jasmine is sick.

174
00:11:21,767 --> 00:11:23,733
But do you always have to be

175
00:11:23,867 --> 00:11:25,767
ang center of the universe?

176
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:27,900
My husband is already spending
all his time

177
00:11:28,033 --> 00:11:29,200
on you and your daughter.

178
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:30,300
And now even the maids

179
00:11:30,433 --> 00:11:32,600
are busy taking care of you?

180
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:34,667
Cathy, Rose, go ahead and put
those down.

181
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,933
Help Thea instead.

182
00:11:37,067 --> 00:11:39,567
She looks like she's struggling
with what she's carrying.

183
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:40,800
Go on.

184
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:43,400
Don't patronize me, Marj.

185
00:11:43,967 --> 00:11:45,200
What are you trying to imply?

186
00:11:45,967 --> 00:11:47,900
That you're the kind,
self-sacrificing one,

187
00:11:48,033 --> 00:11:49,033
and I'm the villain?

188
00:11:49,167 --> 00:11:52,133
Isn't that what you want?
To be the priority?

189
00:11:52,267 --> 00:11:54,300
Here, I'm giving you exactly
what you want.

190
00:11:54,433 --> 00:11:56,100
What nonsense are you talking
about?

191
00:11:59,100 --> 00:12:02,100
Why doesn't your daughter
just die already

192
00:12:02,233 --> 00:12:05,433
so there'd be fewer problems
in this house?

193
00:12:05,567 --> 00:12:06,467
Ow! What the...

194
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,100
Take that back!

195
00:12:08,233 --> 00:12:09,900
- Come on, Marj? Let go of me!
- Take it back!

196
00:12:10,033 --> 00:12:11,067
Take it back!

197
00:12:12,433 --> 00:12:13,400
- I'm getting hurt!
- Now!

198
00:12:13,533 --> 00:12:14,467
- Huh?
- What the hell?

199
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,633
Are you crazy?!

200
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:17,967
I'll break your arm
if you don't take back

201
00:12:18,100 --> 00:12:20,000
what you said about my daughter!

202
00:12:20,133 --> 00:12:21,967
- Don't try me!
- That hurts! Wait!

203
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:25,433
Fine! I'm sorry.

204
00:12:25,567 --> 00:12:27,033
I take it back!

205
00:12:27,167 --> 00:12:32,033
Don't drag my daughter
into your nasty attitude!

206
00:12:35,667 --> 00:12:37,300
We'll handle it, Ma'am.

207
00:12:48,667 --> 00:12:51,200
Is the experimental procedure
safe, Doctor?

208
00:12:51,767 --> 00:12:53,267
Because I'm scared.

209
00:12:53,833 --> 00:12:55,733
I don't want anything bad
to happen to my daughter.

210
00:12:56,733 --> 00:13:00,867
Well, no procedure
is ever 100 percent safe.

211
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:03,233
What you're feeling
is completely normal.

212
00:13:03,367 --> 00:13:07,533
Any parent would worry
in a situation like this.

213
00:13:08,133 --> 00:13:11,333
But I'm more afraid of doing
nothing for her.

214
00:13:11,467 --> 00:13:13,933
If I just wait for things
to get worse,

215
00:13:14,833 --> 00:13:17,567
it's like I'm already accepting
that I'll lose her.

216
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:21,467
So even if Jasmine
only has a small chance...

217
00:13:21,633 --> 00:13:24,567
I'll do anything
for my daughter.

218
00:13:24,700 --> 00:13:26,733
Once you've decided,

219
00:13:26,867 --> 00:13:28,533
I'll arrange the endorsement.

220
00:13:29,367 --> 00:13:32,000
All right, I'll talk
to my husband.

221
00:13:33,033 --> 00:13:36,067
I don't even know
how to explain to him...

222
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:38,067
that we need to do this.

223
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:39,833
We have to take the risk.

224
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:43,933
We have to make a decision.

225
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:46,767
Just let me know.

226
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:52,567
Make sure the vegetables
are soft, okay?

227
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:55,167
- Yes, Ma'am.
- So she can digest them easily.

228
00:13:55,733 --> 00:13:57,300
- Yes, Ma'am!
- Yes, Ma'am..

229
00:14:10,967 --> 00:14:13,600
Ma'am, are you okay?

230
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:15,867
Did you get hurt?

231
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,633
- Oh my God.
- No, I'm fine.

232
00:14:17,767 --> 00:14:19,033
No, Ma'am, I'll handle it.

233
00:14:19,167 --> 00:14:20,067
Please stand up.

234
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,133
- It's okay, I've got it.
- Come on, Ma'am.

235
00:14:21,267 --> 00:14:22,500
- Please get up.
- I'll take care of it.

236
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:25,367
Ma'am, I'll handle it.

237
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:27,767
Are you sure you're okay?

238
00:14:28,533 --> 00:14:30,900
Why, Ma'am?

239
00:14:31,033 --> 00:14:32,067
- Ma'am
- My right eye

240
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:35,233
is getting blurrier
and blurrier.

241
00:14:36,267 --> 00:14:40,633
It's the diabetes,
I'm slowly going blind.

242
00:14:40,767 --> 00:14:43,100
What? You're going blind?

243
00:14:43,233 --> 00:14:44,900
Keep your voice down.

244
00:14:45,633 --> 00:14:48,800
It won't happen right away.

245
00:14:49,967 --> 00:14:53,267
You two, don't tell our
employers.

246
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:54,933
I don't want to lose my job.

247
00:14:55,733 --> 00:14:56,833
Ma'am!

248
00:14:56,967 --> 00:14:58,933
but you need to see a doctor

249
00:14:59,067 --> 00:15:02,567
so it can be treated
before it gets worse.

250
00:15:02,733 --> 00:15:05,200
My condition can't be stopped
anymore.

251
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:07,500
It can only be slowed down.

252
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:10,400
Give that to me.

253
00:15:10,533 --> 00:15:11,400
I'll do it.

254
00:15:11,533 --> 00:15:12,967
I'll do it,
I can handle this.

255
00:15:15,767 --> 00:15:18,500
Jasmine's condition isn't
improving, love.

256
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:20,733
Maybe it's time we consider

257
00:15:20,867 --> 00:15:23,067
the experimental treatment
in Hong Kong.

258
00:15:28,133 --> 00:15:29,233
Hong Kong?

259
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:31,633
Experimental treatment?

260
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:36,333
Edward's friend, the specialist,

261
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:38,000
said Jasmine qualifies

262
00:15:38,133 --> 00:15:40,400
for the experimental procedure.

263
00:15:40,533 --> 00:15:42,067
But it's in Hong Kong.

264
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:45,600
If it's experimental,

265
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:48,400
that means there's a risk
to Jasmine's condition.

266
00:15:48,633 --> 00:15:49,667
It's dangerous.

267
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:50,833
No, no.

268
00:15:50,967 --> 00:15:53,467
Dr. Alvarez himself
recommended it.

269
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,000
He said the risk is low.

270
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,767
A risk is still a risk.

271
00:15:57,900 --> 00:15:59,367
No matter how small it is.

272
00:16:00,567 --> 00:16:03,367
So you'd rather risk
our daughter's life

273
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:07,433
on a procedure
that isn't even guaranteed?

274
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:08,967
Even if Jasmine only
has the tiniest chance

275
00:16:09,133 --> 00:16:10,133
of getting better,

276
00:16:10,267 --> 00:16:11,633
I'm willing to try.

277
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:14,967
I'll consider every option.

278
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:19,900
We can't just sit here watching
Jasmine suffer.

279
00:16:20,667 --> 00:16:22,600
Marj, don't you understand?

280
00:16:23,567 --> 00:16:25,700
Your daughter could die
because of that.

281
00:16:26,367 --> 00:16:27,700
And I'm not willing
to gamble with that.

282
00:16:29,167 --> 00:16:31,400
That's exactly what happened
to the company.

283
00:16:33,567 --> 00:16:36,467
I made changes,
I tried new direction,

284
00:16:37,967 --> 00:16:39,467
now it's all falling apart.

285
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:45,533
Marj, I don't want that
to happen to us.

286
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:48,833
I don't want us to regret it
later.

287
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:51,200
So please...

288
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:53,467
just listen to me.

289
00:16:54,667 --> 00:16:57,833
I'm not your employee
that you get to order around.

290
00:16:59,033 --> 00:17:00,100
I'm a mother.

291
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:04,467
Every decision I make
is for our daughter's good,

292
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:06,267
not to harm her.

293
00:17:07,033 --> 00:17:09,300
And I'm still Jasmine's father.

294
00:17:10,367 --> 00:17:12,867
I'm still the head of this
family.

295
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:16,867
I still have the final say.

296
00:17:41,633 --> 00:17:43,000
Yes, Mom.

297
00:17:43,133 --> 00:17:45,533
The nurse just gave me
my medicine.

298
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,200
<i>Okay, sweetheart,
get some rest, all right?</i>

299
00:17:49,367 --> 00:17:51,633
<i>I'm just going to the pharmacy
to buy some meds.</i>

300
00:17:51,767 --> 00:17:53,467
<i> I'll be right back.</i>

301
00:17:54,967 --> 00:17:56,233
All right, Mom.

302
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:06,800
Ash?

303
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:12,167
- Xander?
- Jasmine!

304
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:14,867
I've finally seen you!

305
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:15,867
Hey.

306
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,067
I can't believe
you guys are here.

307
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:20,967
Sorry, we're only
visiting now, Jasmine.

308
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:23,800
It's hard to catch a time
when your mom isn't here.

309
00:18:26,233 --> 00:18:27,867
Ah, I got you something.

310
00:18:28,867 --> 00:18:30,300
This is your favorite, right?

311
00:18:34,867 --> 00:18:35,967
What's wrong, Jas?

312
00:18:36,967 --> 00:18:39,133
I just don't have much
of an appetite.

313
00:18:41,267 --> 00:18:43,233
Okay, Xander, just set it aside
for now.

314
00:18:43,367 --> 00:18:45,833
Come on!
I bet the food here sucks.

315
00:18:45,967 --> 00:18:47,233
Just try it.

316
00:18:49,167 --> 00:18:51,167
- Okay.
- Yes!

317
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:57,800
What we are selling
is not just a house.

318
00:18:57,967 --> 00:19:02,333
Menagerie Manor is an exclusive
and premiere housing community.

319
00:19:03,233 --> 00:19:06,267
What we are selling is luxury.

320
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:08,733
The feeling of being special.

321
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:12,533
Excuse me.

322
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,300
Excuse me?

323
00:19:15,433 --> 00:19:17,567
Is there a problem, Mr. Castelo?

324
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:19,100
Sorry, boss.

325
00:19:19,233 --> 00:19:22,133
I thought we were here to
discuss strategy.

326
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,900
You've been using exclusivity

327
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:29,900
to sell your properties
for years.

328
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:34,533
But I'm sorry to say,
it's obviously not working.

329
00:19:37,033 --> 00:19:38,433
That's got a lot of fiber.

330
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:45,133
Do you like it?

331
00:19:50,900 --> 00:19:52,333
Hey, don't bother.

332
00:19:53,033 --> 00:19:54,067
I'll do it.

333
00:19:54,933 --> 00:19:57,000
Just sit back,
let me take care of you.

334
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:05,733
Get well soon, okay?

335
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:08,667
So next time
you can hang out with us.

336
00:20:09,067 --> 00:20:11,000
I'll take you anywhere
you want to eat.

337
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:21,833
Why?

338
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:24,400
Do you have a better idea?

339
00:20:25,267 --> 00:20:26,300
Yes.

340
00:20:26,933 --> 00:20:29,900
Let's partner with different
establishments.

341
00:20:30,267 --> 00:20:32,833
Cafés, restaurants...

342
00:20:33,867 --> 00:20:35,700
convenience stores,
retail shops.

343
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:41,333
We can build spaces for them
inside the village.

344
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:45,100
Now imagine
if you were the buyer.

345
00:20:46,133 --> 00:20:48,267
With the added convenience,

346
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:50,433
wouldn't you be more tempted
to purchase a unit?

347
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,933
We're already struggling
to sell units,

348
00:20:55,067 --> 00:20:57,167
and now you want to add more
expenses?

349
00:20:57,300 --> 00:21:00,267
Mr. Torrecampo,
you still don't see it.

350
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:02,567
Once we sell all the units,

351
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:04,667
we'll recover the costs.

352
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:06,867
And the profits will be
even bigger.

353
00:21:07,433 --> 00:21:08,633
It's a big gamble!

354
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:11,333
Yes, it is a big gamble,
but a smart one.

355
00:21:12,967 --> 00:21:16,833
Isn't a leader supposed to have
the balls to take risks?

356
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:20,333
Maybe you should learn
to grow one.

357
00:21:22,467 --> 00:21:23,633
Just ignore him.

358
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,000
Everyone's watching.

359
00:21:47,133 --> 00:21:49,167
- Ma'am!
- Oh?

360
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:50,167
Ma'am.

361
00:21:50,300 --> 00:21:51,533
Where's the Embutido?
I'm excited.

362
00:21:51,667 --> 00:21:53,133
My stomach's been growling
for a while now.

363
00:21:53,267 --> 00:21:54,533
Oh, I'm heating it up.

364
00:21:54,667 --> 00:21:55,800
I'm also scooping you some rice.

365
00:21:55,933 --> 00:21:56,933
Here it is.

366
00:21:57,067 --> 00:21:59,367
It's burning!

367
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:02,033
Oh no! We're gonna start a fire!
Oh my God!

368
00:22:02,833 --> 00:22:04,833
What's going on?

369
00:22:05,633 --> 00:22:07,133
Oh my.

370
00:22:10,633 --> 00:22:11,667
Oh no!

371
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:14,067
No wonder.

372
00:22:14,567 --> 00:22:17,600
There was still aluminum foil
left on the Embutido.

373
00:22:17,767 --> 00:22:21,367
But I removed the wrapper
before I put it in.

374
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:28,000
Ma'am, maybe you didn't notice
there was still some foil left.

375
00:22:29,267 --> 00:22:35,033
Manang, we really can't ignore
your blurry vision anymore.

376
00:22:35,167 --> 00:22:37,433
You can't just do nothing
about it.

377
00:22:37,567 --> 00:22:40,800
You see?
Even with your glasses on,

378
00:22:40,933 --> 00:22:43,233
your vision's still blurry.
You're making mistakes.

379
00:22:43,367 --> 00:22:44,800
Oh dear.

380
00:22:44,933 --> 00:22:47,400
Manang, if you don't want
to see a doctor

381
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:50,433
because it's expensive,
I know someone.

382
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:53,333
In Quiapo, there's a faith
healer I know.

383
00:22:54,133 --> 00:22:55,333
They're really good.

384
00:22:55,933 --> 00:22:58,067
Maybe they can help you.

385
00:23:03,467 --> 00:23:06,400
All right, make sure we bring
all the trash with us, okay?

386
00:23:06,533 --> 00:23:08,367
- Ah, yes, I got it.
- Auntie Marj is gonna kill me

387
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:10,167
if she finds out you were here

388
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:13,267
Thanks so much
for visiting, guys.

389
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:14,900
I really appreciate it.

390
00:23:15,033 --> 00:23:17,667
You don't know how boring
it gets here.

391
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:18,767
Obviously.

392
00:23:18,900 --> 00:23:20,400
How can you live like this?

393
00:23:20,533 --> 00:23:21,567
Come on.

394
00:23:22,533 --> 00:23:23,733
I'm just kidding.

395
00:23:25,433 --> 00:23:26,767
Get well soon, Jas.

396
00:23:28,133 --> 00:23:30,733
So we don't have to keep
sneaking in here.

397
00:23:30,867 --> 00:23:36,433
What he means is so we can hang
out with you again.

398
00:23:37,500 --> 00:23:40,233
Yes, I miss hanging out
with you.

399
00:23:47,433 --> 00:23:48,800
Mom says she's on her way back.

400
00:23:48,933 --> 00:23:51,967
Oh God! We have to go now, Jas.

401
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:53,200
Take care.

402
00:23:53,333 --> 00:23:54,433
Take care, Jas.

403
00:23:54,567 --> 00:23:55,967
- Get well, get well soon.
- Thank you again, guys.

404
00:23:56,133 --> 00:23:57,267
- Okay, go.
- Come on.

405
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:58,633
- Go.
- Get well soon, Jas.

406
00:23:58,767 --> 00:23:59,633
- Hurry!
- Bye, guys.

407
00:23:59,767 --> 00:24:00,800
Bye, Jas!

408
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:09,867
How are you?

409
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:20,900
Nurse?

410
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:22,533
I feel dizzy.

411
00:24:22,667 --> 00:24:24,033
Code blue! Code blue!

412
00:24:27,933 --> 00:24:29,400
Nurse?

413
00:24:29,567 --> 00:24:30,767
What's happening?

414
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:32,000
Nurse! Nurse!

415
00:24:32,133 --> 00:24:33,333
Jas! Jas!

416
00:24:33,467 --> 00:24:34,467
Wait! Jas!

417
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:35,767
Nurse, please!

418
00:24:37,067 --> 00:24:38,367
Sweetheart, just relax.

419
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:39,567
Sweetheart, please.

420
00:24:40,367 --> 00:24:41,900
Oh my God.

421
00:24:42,033 --> 00:24:43,100
Jas.

422
00:24:45,367 --> 00:24:48,100
Jasmine's body is rejecting
her current medications.

423
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:50,000
That's why she had a seizure.

424
00:24:50,700 --> 00:24:52,400
So what should we do now?

425
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:55,900
Well, I think we need
to consider

426
00:24:56,033 --> 00:24:58,367
that experimental treatment
in Hong Kong.

427
00:24:59,467 --> 00:25:01,233
Think about it again,
Mrs. Torrecampo.

428
00:25:03,967 --> 00:25:05,633
I'll go ahead. Excuse me.

429
00:25:05,767 --> 00:25:06,933
Thank you.

430
00:25:21,100 --> 00:25:22,467
Marj?

431
00:25:24,967 --> 00:25:26,133
What happened?

432
00:25:29,567 --> 00:25:32,567
Instead of getting better,

433
00:25:32,700 --> 00:25:34,533
Jasmine seems to be getting
worse.

434
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:38,067
Edward, my heart breaks
for my daughter.

435
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:42,567
I'm so sorry, Marj.

436
00:25:43,867 --> 00:25:49,467
Just tell me if there's anything
I can do...

437
00:25:50,433 --> 00:25:51,633
to help you.

438
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:57,667
I can't stand seeing my daughter
suffer like this.

439
00:25:58,567 --> 00:26:01,033
Maybe I really need to take her
to Hong Kong.

440
00:26:01,633 --> 00:26:03,367
Doesn't Paolo disagree?

441
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:05,700
Let him get mad.

442
00:26:06,767 --> 00:26:09,300
What matters
is my daughter's life.

443
00:26:10,833 --> 00:26:13,600
Not my husband's feelings.

444
00:26:31,267 --> 00:26:33,133
You're booking a flight
to Hong Kong?

445
00:26:33,267 --> 00:26:34,967
I thought we already talked
about this.

446
00:26:35,100 --> 00:26:37,267
Paolo, our daughter
is getting worse.

447
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:40,800
I'm just looking for a way
to save our child.

448
00:26:40,933 --> 00:26:43,433
What if her condition gets worse
because of that?

449
00:26:43,600 --> 00:26:44,600
Is no one going to listen to me?

450
00:26:44,733 --> 00:26:46,567
Do I still not have
a voice here?

451
00:26:47,533 --> 00:26:50,400
Paolo, your wife left
carrying a suitcase.

452
00:26:50,533 --> 00:26:52,333
She said she's taking Jasmine
to Hong Kong.

453
00:26:52,967 --> 00:26:54,133
What?

454
00:26:54,267 --> 00:26:56,800
I'm going to Hong Kong
to follow Marj and Jasmine.

455
00:26:56,933 --> 00:26:58,800
If you abandon this company...

456
00:26:59,767 --> 00:27:01,500
you can forget your position.

457
00:27:01,633 --> 00:27:02,733
You will be like Edward.

458
00:27:02,867 --> 00:27:05,367
You won't even be able to come
back here as a janitor!

459
00:27:05,500 --> 00:27:09,200
Let's see where you, your wife,
and your daughter end up.

460
00:27:09,333 --> 00:27:11,833
My wife defied me
because of you!

461
00:27:11,967 --> 00:27:13,900
Are you Marj's parent
for her to obey you?
